First, clone the repo.

To install the vita-toolchain you require some dependencies:
- autotools (optional)
- make
- install
- a compiler
- an arm compiler (devkitarm r44 or above works fine)

Once you have these, a simple:
./configure && make
sudo make install

Will install the toolchain for you. You can change the install location using the --prefix flag on the ./configure script.
